        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50716",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=frosch",
                        "name": "frosch",
                        "displayName": "Frank Br\u00fcckner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi James,\r\nsorry I can not follow: why you are using a {{Zend_Controller_Request_Http}} instance in your form?\r\n\r\n* {{Zend_Controller_Request_Http::isPost()}} uses {{Zend_Controller_Request_Http::getMethod()}}\r\n* {{Zend_Controller_Request_Http::getMethod()}} uses {{Zend_Controller_Request_Http::getServer()}}\r\n\r\n{code:title=Zend_Controller_Request_Http::getServer()}\r\n\/**\r\n * Retrieve a member of the $_SERVER superglobal\r\n *\r\n * If no $key is passed, returns the entire $_SERVER array.\r\n *\r\n * @param string $key\r\n * @param mixed $default Default value to use if key not found\r\n * @return mixed Returns null if key does not exist\r\n *\/\r\npublic function getServer($key = null, $default = null)\r\n{\r\n    if (null === $key) {\r\n        return $_SERVER;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    return (isset($_SERVER[$key])) ? $_SERVER[$key] : $default;\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nHow it helps in a {{Zend_Form}} object? (?)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=frosch",
                        "name": "frosch",
                        "displayName": "Frank Br\u00fcckner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-05-21T15:48:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-05-21T15:48:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50842",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think the example may be bogus ($form->setMethod('post') has no bearing on the case-sensitivity of the actual HTTP request that results from submitting the form), but [combined with this comment in the PHP manual|http:\/\/ca3.php.net\/manual\/en\/reserved.variables.server.php#95672] it may be worth looking at whether we should still apply the fix?\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-05-29T18:51:16.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-05-29T18:51:16.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50909",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
                        "displayName": "Rob Allen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The correct HTTP method is POST in all caps which is what is tested for.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rob",
                        "name": "rob",
